	keywords = {Brassica napus; Zea mays; Forestry; Magnetic resonance; Magnetic resonance imaging; Plants (botany); Positrons; Soils; Thermal gradients; Throughput; Branching angles; Brassica napus; Carbon transport; Cellular growth process; Differential response; Dynamic changes; Field performance; High throughput; Imaging technology; Integrated approach; Lateral roots; Low temperatures; Natural soils; Novel route; Optical analysis; Petri dish; Phenotyping; Plant breeding; Root growth; Root structure; Root system; Root tip; Root zone temperature; Temperature gradient; Temperature response; Temporal scale; Zea mays; acclimation; canola; ecomorphology; genotype; growth rate; imaging method; maize; phenotype; plant breeding; root architecture; root system; temperature effect; temperature gradient; tomography; Positron emission tomography},
